==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: patina
<hw>pat"ina</hw> <pr>(p⟦acr⟧t"⟦icr⟧*n⟦adot⟧; It.
p⟦aum⟧"t⟦esl⟧*n⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It., fr. L.
<ets>patina</ets> a dish, a pan, a kind of cake. Cf.
<er>Paten</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A dish or plate of metal or
earthenware; a patella.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Fine Arts)</fld> <def>The color or incrustation
which age gives to works of art; especially, the green rust which covers
ancient bronzes, coins, and medals.</def>
<rj><au>Fairholt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>patinate</ent>⟦br⟧
